# KrishiSaathi — Implementation Plan

**Version:** 1.0  
**Author:** Yash Mishra  
**Date:** June 2026

---

## Overview

This implementation plan breaks the KrishiSaathi platform into three phases across 6 months, following an iterative delivery approach. Each phase ends with a deployable release.

---

## Phase 1 — Core MVP (Weeks 1–8)
*Target: Farmers can list crops; buyers can browse and bid; AI detects disease*

### Sprint 1 (Week 1–2): Project Foundation
**Goal:** Repo setup, environment configuration, core auth

Tasks:
- Initialize monorepo: React + Vite frontend, Node.js backend, Python AI service
- Configure TailwindCSS, Framer Motion, React Router
- Set up MongoDB Atlas cluster and Mongoose connection
- Implement User schema (name, email, password, role, location)
- Build POST `/api/auth/register` and POST `/api/auth/login`
- JWT middleware + protected route pattern
- AuthContext in React (login/logout/me)
- Landing page + Login/Register pages (UI)
- i18next setup with en/hi/mr locales
- Configure Cloudinary account and upload utility
- Set up GitHub Actions CI workflow

Deliverable: Working auth flow (register → login → protected dashboard)

### Sprint 2 (Week 3–4): AI Disease Detection
**Goal:** Core AI feature — leaf photo → diagnosis → treatment

Tasks:
- Set up Python FastAPI project structure
- Download PlantVillage dataset (or configure demo mode)
- Implement MobileNetV2 transfer learning (train.py)
- Build `/predict` endpoint accepting multipart image upload
- Implement demo mode with treatments.json fallback
- Build `/health` endpoint
- Create Detection schema in MongoDB
- Build backend route POST `/api/detection/predict` (proxy to AI service)
- Store detection results (image URL via Cloudinary, result JSON)
- Detection history API GET `/api/detection/history`
- Disease Detection page UI (upload, camera, result card with treatment)
- Detection history page

Deliverable: Full disease detection flow end-to-end

### Sprint 3 (Week 5–6): Marketplace & Real-time Bidding
**Goal:** Farmers list crops; buyers bid in real-time

Tasks:
- Build Crop schema with all fields (photos, location, status, bids)
- CRUD routes for `/api/crops`
- Image upload for crop photos via Cloudinary + Multer
- Socket.IO setup on backend (bid rooms per listing)
- Bid schema and bid-placement logic
- Highest bid tracking + outbid event broadcast
- Marketplace listing page UI (grid view, search, filter)
- Crop detail page with bid history + live bid feed
- "Place Bid" modal with amount input
- Farmer's listings dashboard
- "Create Listing" form with voice upload trigger

Deliverable: End-to-end real-time bidding marketplace

### Sprint 4 (Week 7–8): Orders & Payments
**Goal:** Buyers can place orders and pay via Razorpay

Tasks:
- Order schema with payment sub-document
- Razorpay integration: create order (backend) + verify signature
- POST `/api/orders`, GET `/api/orders/my`
- Order status update flow (farmer confirms → ships → delivered)
- Order history UI for buyers and farmers
- Payment status page (success/failure)
- Email notification stubs (console log for MVP)
- Basic admin view (order list)

Deliverable: Full purchase + payment flow

**Phase 1 Milestone: MVP Launch on Vercel + Render + MongoDB Atlas**

---

## Phase 2 — Feature Expansion (Weeks 9–16)
*Target: Agri Store, Insurance, AI Chat, News/Prices, full multilingual*

### Sprint 5 (Week 9–10): Agri Store
**Goal:** E-commerce for seeds, fertilizers, tools

Tasks:
- StoreProduct schema and admin seeding script
- Store product routes: GET `/api/store/products`, GET `/api/store/products/:id`
- Cart state management (React, localStorage-backed for MVP)
- Checkout with Razorpay (reuse payment infra)
- StoreOrder schema and routes
- Agri Store page UI (product grid, categories, search)
- Product detail page
- Cart sidebar / drawer
- Store order confirmation page

Deliverable: Functional agri-store with payment

### Sprint 6 (Week 11–12): Crop Insurance Module
**Goal:** Farmers discover and apply for insurance schemes

Tasks:
- InsuranceScheme schema + seed 5–8 popular schemes (PMFBY, etc.)
- Insurance routes: GET `/api/insurance/schemes`, GET `/api/insurance/schemes/:id`
- InsuranceApplication schema + POST `/api/insurance/apply`
- Insurance browsing page UI (filter by crop, state, type)
- Scheme detail page (coverage, eligibility, documents)
- Application form (crop, land area, season)
- Application status tracking

Deliverable: Insurance discovery and application flow

### Sprint 7 (Week 13–14): AI Chat Support & News
**Goal:** 24/7 farming assistant and live market intelligence

Tasks:
- AI Chat backend integration (OpenAI/Claude API proxy route)
- ChatHistory schema and persistence
- Multilingual chat (pass language header to AI API)
- Chat UI: fixed chat window, message bubbles, typing indicator
- Krishi Samachar: fetch from agri news API (e.g., newsdata.io filtered to agriculture)
- Mandi price feed: integrate via agmarknet API or scrape cache
- News cache schema with 1-hour TTL
- News page UI (news cards, market price table)
- Weather widget (OpenWeatherMap API, user location)

Deliverable: AI chat and live news/prices features

### Sprint 8 (Week 15–16): Multilingual Completion + Profile
**Goal:** Full localization across all features; user profile management

Tasks:
- Complete all i18n translations (en, hi, mr) for all new pages (Phases 1+2)
- Language switcher in navbar
- Store language preference in user profile
- User profile page UI (photo upload, name, phone, location, language)
- PUT `/api/auth/profile` endpoint
- Cloudinary profile photo upload
- Password change in profile
- Breadcrumb navigation, back buttons for low-tech users
- User onboarding flow (role selection post-signup)

Deliverable: Fully localized platform with profile management

**Phase 2 Milestone: Full Feature Release**

